laboratory_examinations.findings: The appendix is visualized in the right lower quadrant and is abnormal. It measures up to 11 mm, fluid-filled with mucosal hyperenhancement. There is periappendiceal fat stranding. A tiny focus of fluid adjacent to the base of the appendix is noted, not clearly intraluminal. The liver is normal in appearance, without focal lesions. The gallbladder is decompressed, without cholelithiasis. Other abdominal organs are normal with no hydronephrosis and no free fluid or free air in the abdomen.
